bug.short_desc: Last selected row remains marked if another row is selected by clicking outside the table pane

long_desc.thetext:
If a row in a table is selected by clicking on the row and then another row is selected by clicking outside the table pane at the right side where no column is displayed anymore the new row is selected without unmarking the last selected row (light blue).
This can be observed in:
http://demo.qooxdoo.org/html/test/Table_1.html
1) click into the cell row 1 colum1 2) click into the "cell free" area outside the "Boolean test" column at height of another row (not row 1).
A screen snapshot is attached which shows the bug.
Created attachment 77 screen snapshot showing the bug
I think the "cell free area" should not react to mouse click events.
